This is the main directory of the source code of the Cloning library.

In order to create the Eclipse project, run "mvn eclipse:eclipse". You will
need Maven 2.2 or higher to run the above command. Please visit the Maven
website for detailed instructions:

http://maven.apache.org/

Once the command has been successfully executed, you may simply import the
project to your workspace, using the included launch configurations to run
some of the test suites. Alternatively, you can right-click on a test suite
or the whole project and select "Run As > JUnit Test".

Happy hacking!

--- Only for maintainers ---

To generate a signed release bundle for the Sonatype Central Publisher Portal,
run:

mvn -B clean package gpg:sign repository:bundle-create

Before running this, make sure you have a private GPG key available and export
its passphrase for non-interactive signing:

export MAVEN_GPG_PASSPHRASE="your-gpg-passphrase"

If you do not already have a key, create one first:

gpg --batch --pinentry-mode loopback --passphrase "$MAVEN_GPG_PASSPHRASE" \
  --quick-generate-key "Your Name <you@example.com>" ed25519 sign 0

Publish to Sonatype Central with:

mvn -B -P sonatype-deploy deploy

This requires a Sonatype Central user token in your Maven settings, for example:

<server>
  <id>central</id>
  <username>YOUR_SONATYPE_TOKEN_USERNAME</username>
  <password>YOUR_SONATYPE_TOKEN_PASSWORD</password>
</server>

Create the token from the Sonatype Central Portal before publishing. Please do
not forget to distribute the public key to a key server (for example
hkp://pgp.mit.edu) if the signed bundle is to be accepted in Maven Central.
 